1
00:01:37,009 --> 00:01:39,950
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:42,039
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:46,750
If you're sleepy, take a nap in the back.

4
00:01:47,470 --> 00:01:49,920
If you're done drinking, put the lid back and place it here.

5
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,600
Don't spill water on yourself.

6
00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:06,190
After finishing this trip

7
00:02:06,190 --> 00:02:07,700
and deducting all the expenses,

8
00:02:07,730 --> 00:02:08,870
we'll have about 700 yuan left.

9
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,660
While on the road,

10
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:17,900
I've been thinking about something.

11
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:21,350
Driving a truck is really tough.

12
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:22,990
Let's

13
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:24,230
work hard for a few years.

14
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:26,710
After we put our son through college

15
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,130
and he finds a good job,

16
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:30,030
we can take a breather.

17
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,079
We'll stop driving

18
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:32,430
and take a good rest.

19
00:02:40,329 --> 00:02:41,700
Or

20
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:44,390
we can buy a small ship.

21
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:49,310
It doesn't matter how many shipping deals we can get.

22
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:52,670
If we can't get any deals, we'll just enjoy the scenery on the ship.

23
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:53,710
You like the idea?

24
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,690
Mom.

25
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:23,940
You're back.

26
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,840
Son, you're back.

27
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,750
Where's Dad?

28
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,040
Sleeping.

29
00:03:34,270 --> 00:03:35,000
Did everything go smoothly?

30
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,520
Yeah.

31
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:41,829
The client wanted to dock my pay because I arrived late.

32
00:03:41,850 --> 00:03:44,650
Your dad rolled up his sleeves and made him pay the full amount.

33
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:46,750
He's like your bodyguard.

34
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:47,820
Great.

35
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:49,990
Luckily, it didn't come to blows.

36
00:03:49,990 --> 00:03:51,079
Otherwise,

37
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,430
the money we earned

38
00:03:52,550 --> 00:03:53,579
couldn't even cover the medical bills.

39
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,750
Dad is experienced in this.

40
00:03:55,950 --> 00:03:57,120
Back when he was a seafarer,

41
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,270
there were also people who tried to skip out on paying.

42
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,350
He just got physical.

43
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:09,090
What's wrong, Mom?

44
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:10,570
Did you two have a fight?

45
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:12,830
No.

46
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:16,500
I wish we had.

47
00:04:17,970 --> 00:04:19,750
Your dad didn't give me the chance.

48
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:20,890
What do you mean?

49
00:04:24,420 --> 00:04:25,420
During the trip,

50
00:04:25,710 --> 00:04:27,490
over 2,000 kilometers in total,

51
00:04:28,330 --> 00:04:29,730
your father kept a long face

52
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,040
the whole time.

53
00:04:33,030 --> 00:04:35,159
And he said to me a total of maybe…

54
00:04:35,670 --> 00:04:36,880
200 words?

55
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,370
Boss Xie.

56
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:12,280
Mr. Shao.

57
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:13,260
Are you off work?

58
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,310
I thought it was you from afar.

59
00:05:15,330 --> 00:05:16,060
It's really you.

60
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:19,730
You're in charge of

61
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:20,940
buying groceries now?

62
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:24,360
Well, Haihong

63
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:26,390
is busy driving the truck.

64
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,270
I'll do what I can to help.

65
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:29,200
Yeah.

66
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,030
Well,

67
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:31,580
how's the publication of your book going?

68
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:35,350
It's in the works.

69
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,270
I don't have any publishing experience,

70
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,110
so I'm learning as I go.

71
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:39,170
Oh, right.

72
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:41,480
There's something I wanted to talk to you about.

73
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:43,340
Can we have a talk here?

74
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:44,770
Okay.

75
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,530
Come, sit here.

76
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:45,950
Alright.

77
00:05:46,659 --> 00:05:47,420
Sit.

78
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:51,190
Here is the thing.

79
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:53,020
I have a suggestion

80
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,940
that might seem immature.

81
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,960
I'd like to share it with you

82
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,000
to see if it's feasible.

83
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:01,410
You're being so polite. What's it?

84
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,210
You know, every year, many people

85
00:06:04,810 --> 00:06:06,590
drown in the canal.

86
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:09,190
Yesterday, another person drowned upstream near Liu Village.

87
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:11,540
No one is willing to retrieve the body.

88
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,830
Here's what I'm thinking.

89
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,940
Could you consider being an initiator

90
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:19,070
to get some volunteers

91
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,900
to form a canal rescue team

92
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:22,490
that helps those

93
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:24,390
who fall into the water?

94
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:25,560
What do you think?

95
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:27,910
Hold on, M-Mr. Shao.

96
00:06:27,910 --> 00:06:30,040
What exactly are you getting at?

97
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,540
Here's the thing.

98
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:35,550
As you know, the authorities are currently applying for

99
00:06:35,550 --> 00:06:37,190
World Heritage status for the canal.

100
00:06:37,990 --> 00:06:39,290
The heritage is not the canal

101
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:41,440
but the canal culture.

102
00:06:41,909 --> 00:06:43,230
Speaking of culture,

103
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:45,550
look at our Flower Street.

104
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:46,930
What culture does it have?

105
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:51,060
There were a few famous local female entertainers in history,

106
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:52,300
but we can't

107
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,650
use romantic tales to make our case.

108
00:06:55,659 --> 00:06:56,510
However,

109
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,560
with good people who did good things,

110
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:01,350
we can say this is a town

111
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:02,640
with kind-hearted folks.

112
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:05,300
That could be a characteristic of Flower Street,

113
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:05,890
right?

114
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,270
Mr. Shao,

115
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:13,010
are you planning to write and publish something?

116
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,050
No.

117
00:07:14,860 --> 00:07:17,430
Good people and good deeds

118
00:07:17,450 --> 00:07:19,870
are highly commendable.

119
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,050
You'll do good things,

120
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,180
and I'll praise you.

121
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:23,480
It's a win-win.

122
00:07:23,790 --> 00:07:26,050
Then I should get half of the writing fee, right?

123
00:07:26,890 --> 00:07:28,530
Forget about that little bit of money.

124
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,250
What matters is the honor.

125
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:34,830
Alright, it's settled then.

126
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:37,060
The honor goes to you,

127
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,580
and the writing fee goes to me.

128
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,110
If you say so,

129
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:43,909
you're making me speechless.

130
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,990
I'm just joking with you.

131
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:48,470
No matter what,

132
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:49,640
this is a serious matter.

133
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:50,430
After I go home,

134
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,230
I need to discuss it with my wife.

135
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:54,090
I can only do it if she agrees.

136
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:54,700
Alright.

137
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,340
Then I'll wait for your reply.

138
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,210
If the canal gets World Heritage status,

139
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,950
it'll be able

140
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:03,760
to flourish again.

141
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:05,040
By then,

142
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,300
you can truly return to the river.

143
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:08,950
Alright.

144
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:10,230
I'll be going.

145
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:11,360
See you.

146
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,070
Bye, Boss Xie.

147
00:08:42,049 --> 00:08:42,820
Boss Xie.

148
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:44,280
What are you doing here?

149
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:46,460
I came out for some fresh air.

150
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:48,900
You're drinking?

151
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:49,630
I'll grab a few more bottles.

152
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,540
A few more.

153
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:01,420
How's everything? Good?

154
00:09:02,570 --> 00:09:03,710
Just so-so.

155
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:07,590
It's still cold.

156
00:09:10,870 --> 00:09:11,830
How about you?

157
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:13,410
How's the long-haul driving going?

158
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:21,060
Compared to seafaring,

159
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:22,520
it's much more tiring.

160
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:23,350
Is that so?

161
00:09:23,450 --> 00:09:24,590
With seafaring,

162
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:26,060
ships don't go very fast,

163
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:27,300
right?

164
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,460
You don't have to

165
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:30,830
stay focused all the time.

166
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:32,110
Driving is different.

167
00:09:32,330 --> 00:09:34,810
When driving, you always have to keep your eyes on the road.

168
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:37,240
After a whole day,

169
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:38,920
you're sore all over,

170
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,820
and your head buzzes.

171
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,230
It's not so unbearable

172
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,190
as long as you can make money.

173
00:09:45,830 --> 00:09:46,460
Right?

174
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:51,270
Is your supermarket going well?

175
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:52,550
Kind of.

176
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:55,430
I can make about 200 yuan a day.

177
00:09:55,450 --> 00:09:56,250
That's pretty good.

178
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,000
Yeah.

179
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:01,160
Your wife must be happy now.

180
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,100
I guess you could say that.

181
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:07,950
I haven't been told off for over half a month.

182
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:10,050
To be honest, I'm not used to it.

183
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,110
That's not good for your health.

184
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:14,670
I'll remind Yan

185
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:16,680
to nag you more often.

186
00:10:16,710 --> 00:10:17,230
No, no, no.

187
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:18,400
To give you a hard time.

188
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:19,950
Will that make you feel better?

189
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:20,830
Boss Xie, I'm begging you.

190
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:21,310
Please.

191
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,470
These days,

192
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,000
every time we fight,

193
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,790
it takes hours to appease her.

194
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,510
I don't mind groveling a bit,

195
00:10:29,090 --> 00:10:32,330
but my lower back can't take it.

196
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:38,170
My lower back can't take it.

197
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,470
It can't?

198
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,530
Well, Mr. Shao

199
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,190
made a suggestion to me.

200
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:46,770
He said I should

201
00:10:46,810 --> 00:10:49,560
form a canal rescue team.

202
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,480
Are you interested?

203
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:53,830
Rescue team?

204
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:00,910
O-Okay.

205
00:11:01,310 --> 00:11:02,120
Well,

206
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:05,050
if you want me in, I'm in.

207
00:11:05,330 --> 00:11:05,950
Right?

208
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:09,680
I know I can count on you.

209
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:12,770
As long as it doesn't affect my business.

210
00:11:17,870 --> 00:11:18,710
Boss Xie,

211
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:20,770
don't you need to drive the truck?

212
00:11:21,710 --> 00:11:23,080
Does your wife know about this?

213
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:33,560
Do you have cigarettes?

214
00:11:33,950 --> 00:11:34,830
Yes.

215
00:11:34,830 --> 00:11:35,750
Give me one.

216
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:40,660
Here.

217
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:58,410
Who are you bowing to?

218
00:11:58,430 --> 00:11:59,310
The river god.

219
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:00,790
Didn't Mr. Zhou say

220
00:12:00,830 --> 00:12:03,920
the official from the Qing dynasty is the river god here?

221
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:05,920
We should pay our respects.

222
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:07,460
Of course.

223
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,910
Oh, River God,

224
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:10,960
I'm begging you.

225
00:12:11,150 --> 00:12:12,650
Please make

226
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:15,910
this canal prosper again.

227
00:12:15,930 --> 00:12:17,040
Prosper again.

228
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,190
Prosper again.

229
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:21,070
Let us return to our ships.

230
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,230
Return to our ships.

231
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:23,330
Return…

232
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,010
People like us

233
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:26,990
love the smells of kerosene

234
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:27,910
and diesel.

235
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:29,400
We love those smells.

236
00:12:29,430 --> 00:12:30,470
We love the roars

237
00:12:30,490 --> 00:12:33,210
of the engine.

238
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:33,960
Right.

239
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:34,690
Please.

240
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:35,610
We love that sound.

241
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:36,390
Please.

242
00:12:36,410 --> 00:12:37,160
We beg you.

243
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:38,590
Bless us.

244
00:12:38,850 --> 00:12:40,140
Please.

245
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:41,440
Please.

246
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,140
What are you doing?

247
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:08,090
Why are you making all that noise?

248
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,240
How can I sleep?

249
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:10,060
It's late at night.

250
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:11,960
Get on the bed and sleep.

251
00:13:11,980 --> 00:13:13,920
Why are you fiddling with that? Are you crazy?

252
00:13:34,070 --> 00:13:34,870
What's wrong?

253
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:39,920
You should go back to the canal.

254
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,160
I can see it.

255
00:13:44,180 --> 00:13:46,020
You're like a fish.

256
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,190
You can't survive without water.

257
00:13:48,230 --> 00:13:50,480
What if you get sick from holding it in?

258
00:13:51,190 --> 00:13:52,310
I'm not holding anything in.

259
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,600
I'm serious.

260
00:14:01,990 --> 00:14:04,120
Yuling said Mr. Shao wants you

261
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:05,520
to form a canal rescue team, right?

262
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,740
Yeah.

263
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,670
I haven't decided whether to do it or not.

264
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:12,180
Do it.

265
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,030
As long as you're happy,

266
00:14:15,630 --> 00:14:16,510
I'll support you.

267
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,920
Is this a prank?

268
00:14:33,990 --> 00:14:35,210
This family

269
00:14:35,710 --> 00:14:37,510
used to rely entirely on you.

270
00:14:38,430 --> 00:14:39,020
But now,

271
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:41,770
I can share your burden.

272
00:14:42,630 --> 00:14:43,750
In the future, our son

273
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,400
will surely be successful.

274
00:14:47,430 --> 00:14:48,230
Xie Tiancheng,

275
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:51,670
I'm asking you

276
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,830
to keep your spirits up.

277
00:14:58,310 --> 00:14:59,100
I will.

278
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:08,410
I married you

279
00:15:09,990 --> 00:15:11,510
not because you were rich.

280
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:15,360
It was just because you were nice and righteous.

281
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:17,310
Even if you only had

282
00:15:18,230 --> 00:15:19,440
ten cents on you,

283
00:15:20,070 --> 00:15:20,740
you'd still look

284
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:22,350
like a boss.

285
00:15:25,430 --> 00:15:26,990
The vibes you gave

286
00:15:28,690 --> 00:15:30,730
fascinated me back then.

287
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:39,220
So you must not

288
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,390
lose those spirits.

289
00:15:51,310 --> 00:15:53,830
I won't lose them. I won't.

290
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,110
Do you understand what I'm saying?

291
00:15:57,110 --> 00:15:58,190
I do.

292
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:04,000
